    <text id="B2007T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Hunt introduces two teachers who are en route to take up posts in Staunton.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    American Missionary Association,<lb/>No. 61 John Street,
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Orlando">O.</abbr> Brown<lb/><abbr
                            expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst. Comr.</abbr> of Bureau Freedmen</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-11-08"><abbr expan="November">Nov.</abbr> 8 1865</date>
                        <name type="place">New York,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>This will introduce you to Misses Williams and Dewey, whom we have appointed for
                    Staunton. If they need any assistance will you have the kindness to extend to
                    them the necessary courtesies they may require, and much oblige,</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully yours</salute>
                    <signed>Sam'l Hunt<lb/><abbr expan="Superintendent">Supt</abbr> of <abbr
                            expan="Education">Ed</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
